[normal]5.3[bold] 
[normal]LTB’s were set up to secure devolved major schemes funding
[normal] from 
[normal]DfT
[normal].
[normal] A
[normal]lthough 
[normal]Dft
[normal] confirmed there 
[normal]is a significant increase in major schemes funding, 
[normal]some 
[normal]33% less 
[normal]major schemes 
[normal]funding 
[normal]was committed 
[normal]to the 
[normal]current priority schemes than the indicative amounts set out 
[normal]earlier.
[normal]  This was 
[normal]most
[normal] disappointing and for our area, as the Aut
[normal]horities are keen to make progress on the priority schemes
[normal] to support continued growth
[normal], the authorities agreed to deliver 6 
[normal]priority 
[normal]schemes. 
[normal]However in order to 
[normal]deliver theses, some 80% of the funding is being sourced
[normal] f
[normal]r
[normal]o
[normal]m the local authorities, 
[normal]mostly
[normal] th
[normal]rough prudential borrowing. In addition there was little or no money available for scheme development or business case development so local partners have had to take on thos
[normal]e costs. In ou
[normal]r case, the LEP has been most supportive and stepped in to cover the 
